Play Resumes at U.S. Open Tennis Tournament After Two Days of Rainouts

-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 
2011-09-08T15:14:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/play-resumes-at-u-s-open-tennis-tournament-after-two-days-of-rainouts.html
Play is under way at the U.S. Open
tennis tournament after rain wiped out all but 10 games in the
past two days.  Defending-champion  Rafael Nadal  of  Spain  took the court at
Arthur Ashe Stadium in  New York  trailing  Gilles Muller  of
Luxembourg 3-0 in one of three fourth-round matches that started
yesterday.  Andy Roddick  of the U.S. leads  David Ferrer  of Spain
3-1 and Andy Murray of Britain holds a 2-1 lead over Donald
Young of the U.S.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  